    thinking: "**Defining Website Structure**\n\nI\'ve outlined the core framework for the \"MOVE\" NGO website. I\'m focusing on the navigation elements: home, about, projects, and contact us. Next, I\'ll integrate the donation portal functionality into the website\'s architecture, ensuring a seamless user experience.\n\n\n**Refining Tech Choices**\n\nI\'m now carefully considering the technology stack. Integrating the volunteer application and donation form has led me to evaluate the need for Firebase. Client-side SPA with local storage offers a compelling balance of interactivity and simplicity. The admin dashboard would be great.\n\n\n**Evaluating Data Storage Options**\n\nI\'m now deep-diving into data storage. Firebase seems overkill for a promotional website, so I\'m pivoting to client-side solutions. I\'m exploring localStorage for forms, alongside React state, to maintain interactivity and avoid external dependencies, focusing on high fidelity and simplicity.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will start by viewing the `metadata.json` and `package.json` files to understand the project structure, configuration, and dependencies. I will then update the application profile to match our NGO, **MOVE (Pertubuhan Sukarelawan Harapan Malaysia)**."
