  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Listing Interactive Components**\n\nI\'m currently focused on defining the interactive elements for the project. I\'ve begun to outline the key components: Home, About, Projects, Donation Portal, Volunteer Form, and Contact Us. Also considering the Admin Panel, including the possibility of integrating an Admin Simulation Panel.\n\n\n**Designing Simulated States**\n\nI\'m now detailing the implementation of simulated submissions and their states. I\'m building interactive forms and states, aiming for persistent simulated data within the browser session. I\'m exploring a React Context or a clean state provider, likely a custom `/src/context/StateContext.tsx`. This will keep the Admin Panel in sync with volunteer applications and donation counters. The context will include `applications` (with preloaded simulated ones), and `donations`.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create a unified State Context file (`/src/context/StateContext.tsx`) to handle the client-side state dynamically. When users write a message in **Contact Us**, submit a **Volunteer Application**, or make a **Donation**, all submitted records will instantly sync to a local state store (`localStorage` powered) and be viewable in a real-time admin portal log! This gives the application top-tier interactive fidelity. Let\'s create this file."
