    thinking: "**Designing Donation Portal**\n\nI\'m now focused on building the `/src/components/DonationPortal.tsx` file. I\'ve designed an elegant multi-step layout. Step 1: choosing the donation amount, Step 2: Supporter details, and finally, Step 3: a fast simulated settlement payment process.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/DonationPortal.tsx`, which implements the robust donation checkout hub for **MOVE**. It includes:\n- **Progress Checkout Stages**:\n  - *Stage 1 (Budget Allocation)*: Select suggested impact thresholds (specifically tailored to project materials like RM35 for youth books, RM100 for sand filters, RM250 for solar grids) or type a custom contribution. Supporters can designate specific active projects from a dropdown.\n  - *Stage 2 (Donor Credentials)*: Enter name, email, and choose if they want to publish as \"Anonymous\" or make it recurring monthly.\n  - *Stage 3 (Simulated Gateway)*: Choose credit card validation, FPX local Malaysian direct network transfers, or PayPal.\n- **Victory Certificate Screen**: Displays a mock receipt with registration ID confirmation, and live trigger animations.\n- **Live Supporter Wall**: A real-time feeds sidebar querying our state context. When the user successfully checks out, their donation immediately appends on screen as the top supporter with total session counters recalculating!\n\nLet\'s create the file."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 115248990
    }
