  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Developing the Admin Panel**\n\nI\'m making strong headway now that the core file structure is in place. Creating `/src/components/AdminPanel.tsx` is underway, and will facilitate user switching in a smooth manner. The contact form component is also in the works. This includes a custom form with Kuala Lumpur office details. I\'ll include a map placeholder and social links for completeness.\n\n\n**Revising Scope Restraints**\n\nI\'ve hit a conceptual snag. My initial instinct to build a dedicated \"Organizer Dashboard\" is a scope violation! The instructions are clear: no unsolicited features, no separate admin tabs. However, it\'s possible to integrate the review panels directly into existing components. Now, I\'m refactoring my approach to incorporate volunteer file reviews and donation summaries within the current application structure, without creating redundant systems. It\'s a cleaner solution!\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/components/ContactUs.tsx`. It provides contact coordinates for **MOVE** (Pertubuhan Sukarelawan Harapan Malaysia) in Kuala Lumpur, a visually polished message entry form, social coordinate cards, and an interactive layout mock representing our headquarters marker. Let\'s create this file."
