  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Summarizing Achievements!**\n\nI\'m pleased to report that the application has been built successfully, passing all checks with flying colors. It appears to perfectly fulfill the user\'s requirements. Now, I\'m turning my attention to summarizing these accomplishments using the \"Symmetric simple/complex proportional summaries guidelines.\" My focus is on the tone of these summaries.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have designed and built the promotional website for **MOVE** (known officially in Malaysia as ***Pertubuhan Sukarelawan Harapan Malaysia***), a registered NGO providing local and international youth volunteer opportunities. \n\nThe website uses a high-contrast warm-light palette\342\200\224utilizing raw emerald greens, warm ambers, deep charcoal typography, and premium off-white linen backgrounds (`FAF9F5`). It incorporates modern typography through **Space Grotesk** and **Inter**, framed by elegant negative space and transition animations powered by `motion`.\n\nHere is a summary of the designed components and integrated features:\n\n### 1. \360\237\217\241 Home\n*   **Hero Canvas**: Centered visual layout displaying the official registered organization name alongside primary CTAs to volunteer or donate.\n*   **Dynamic Stats Ticker**: Animates total volunteer hours, countries involved, and lists the session\'s live portal donation totals updating dynamically.\n*   **Core Philosophy Board**: Detailed card blocks describing the organization\'s unique co-creation development formulas rather than standard top-down charity.\n*   **Testimonial Slider**: Slideway system demonstrating first-person accounts of Orang Asli community council headers and overseas youth volunteers.\n\n### 2. \360\237\221\245 About Us\n*   **Official Credentials Profile**: Displays metadata documenting the organization\'s legal ID registration numbers validated by the registrar of societies.\n*   **Vision & Mission Statements**: Elegant side-by-side modules detailing structural community and environmental development blueprints.\n*   **Chronological Milestones**: Intercultural history timeline capturing key expansion steps inside Malaysia and Cambodia since 2015.\n*   **Stateful FAQ Accordions**: Interactive, collapsible modules handling policy inquiries such as safety, lodging arrangements, and transparent fee structures.\n\n### 3. \360\237\223\202 Projects Grid Catalog\n*   **Filter Console**: Implements reactive search tags where users can filter active projects by focus category (e.g., *Environment, Culture, Community*) or region layout (*Domestic Malaysia* vs *International*).\n*   **Actionable Detailed Modals**: Clicking any campaign triggers an overlay displaying local village elders, technical skills required, duration vacancies, and co-creation costs.\n*   **Interlinked Actions**: Inside the details panel, candidates can click **\"Apply as Volunteer\"** or **\"Sponsor with a Donation\"**, which closes the modal, sets the target program option, and routes to respective sections instantly.\n\n### 4. \360\237\222\263 Donation Portal (RM & USD)\n*   **3-Stage Checkout Form**: Secures simulated processing by selecting targeted presets (e.g., *RM35 for books, RM100 for sandfilters, RM250 for solar grids*), entering supporter email addresses, and choosing payment channels (such as credit card form mockups or local Malaysian *FPX direct debit* selectors).\n*   **Live Supporter Wall**: Tracks recent backing history from our coordinated state context. When you complete a simulated checked-out donation, it dynamically appends to the top of the feed with updated counters.\n\n### 5. \360\237\223\235 Volunteer Enlistment Form\n*   **Recruitment Dossier**: Captures personal dimensions (nationality, WhatsApp, age ranges) alongside skill checklists (such as eco-gardening, woodwork, marine diving, and tutoring).\n*   **Passport Badge Generator**: Submitting an application compiles a custom green candidate ID badge detailing queued schedules and assigned project titles.\n*   **Interactive Recruits Queue**: View lists of incoming applicants on the side column to trace submitted registration records.\n\n### 6. \360\237\223\236 Contact Us\n*   **Headquarters Coordinates**: Outlines the official central clubhouse address next to the National Mosque in Kuala Lumpur, alongside simulated email and phone widgets.\n*   **Abstract Maps Display**: A visual mockup framing real-time office pinpoints and active transit instructions.\n*   **Dynamic Correspondence Log**: Captures partner inquiries (e.g., *CSR sponsorships and university connections*) and logs successful message transmissions.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 56713651
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
